snippet.title: Flappy Golf
snippet.description: Flappy Golf is the perfect mash-up of Flappy Bird and Stickman Golf, and adds up to a must-have free game with tons of content.

snippet.title: Super Stickman Golf 2
snippet.description: If you liked the first Stickman golf game and want new levels, new obstacles, and new power-ups, Super Stickman Golf 2 is a worthy sequel.

snippet.title: 2015 Volkswagen Golf GTE
snippet.description: The 2015 Volkswagen Golf GTE remixes the GTI's 200-hp output with a plug-in hybrid power-train, blending performance with 130-mpg efficiency.

snippet.title: 2014 Volkswagen Golf R
snippet.description: It's been a while since I've been excited about any variation of VW's Golf, but the latest Golf R revealed at the 2013 International Motor Show in Frankfurt has captured my attention.

snippet.title: Lenovo IdeaCentre B750
snippet.description: A refreshing new way to look at all-in-one desktops, the Lenovo B750's Blu-ray-friendly, extra-wide display is great for movies (if you add some extra software), and games greatly benefit from a wider field of view. It's different, and fun to use, but it cries out for a touch screen.

snippet.title: Nintendo 3DS XL
snippet.description: Three years in, the Nintendo 3DS handheld has become a seriously good game device -- especially for fans of Nintendo's classic gaming franchises -- and the XL is the one you should buy.

snippet.title: 2012 Volkswagen Golf R
snippet.description: The 2012 Volkswagen Golf R is a blast to drive on curvy roads, but can also handle the everyday routine, offering solid, if not cutting-edge, cabin tech features.

snippet.title: Fire Game Controller
snippet.description: Get ready for living-room gaming, Amazon-style: a new controller aims to bring games to the big screen with Fire TV.

snippet.title: Volkswagen Golf SportWagen on the way (pictures)
snippet.description: Volkswagen showed off a Golf SportWagen concept at the New York auto show, but this one is definitely coming out as a production model next year.
